(fifthQuint)Effectiveness of NEURAPAS Balance in Children With Nervous Restlessness.

 Purpose: To document data on effectiveness of NEURAPAS(R) balance (NPB) in the treatment of nervous restlessness in children aged 6 to 12.

 Patients and methods: A prospective, non-interventional, non-randomized, observational study conducted in German pediatric practices.

 Each patient is treated with NPB.

 No placebo group is established.

 As subjective criteria to document course and severity of symptoms, a questionnaire on 13 common symptoms of nervous restlessness and a Visual Analogue Scale (VAS) is used.

 As an objective criterion, a standardized questionnaire (Parent Child Behaviour Checklist (CBCL/4-18)) is completed.

 Choice and doses of therapy are at the respective physician's discretion.

 The planned treatment and observation period is 2 - 4 weeks.

